\"summary\\\":[{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Double-checking method invocation**\\\\n\\\\nI’m looking into using `Method.invoke` with variable arguments, particularly focusing on the last argument as `new Object[0]`. For a reflected method that takes parameters like `[Method,Object,Object[]]`, using an arguments array of length 3 with the last element as `Object[0]` seems correct due to compile-time varargs. However, I'm wondering if it's even necessary to pass it as `(Object) new Object[0]`. Let me think about that!\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"Refined the dedicated active-class test file:\\n\\n- `tests/src/com.diffplug.durian/durian-core/1.2.0/src/test/java/com_diffplug_durian/durian_core/ThrowablesTest.java`\\n\\nChanges:\\n- Kept the public `Throwables.lazyStackTrace(...)` behavioral coverage.\\n- Added a targeted test that invokes Durian’s internal non-throwing method invoker with `Throwables.lazyStackTraceIsLazy()` as the supplied method, so execution should reach:\\n\\n`Throwables.invokeAccessibleNonThrowingMethod(Throwables.java:291)`\\n\\nI did not compile or run tests, per instruction.\", \"textSignature\": \"{\\\"v\\\":1,\\\"id\\\":\\\"msg_08d01039b9a4abe80169f4d600167c8194a2df06ab4dfdc71a\\\",\\\"phase\\\":\\\"final_answer\\\"}\"}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 854, \"output\": 825, \"cacheRead\": 24576, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 26255, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"stop\", \"timestamp\": 1777653235072, \"responseId\": \"resp_08d01039b9a4abe80169f4d5f3684c8194a9c357068e787ca2\"}}\n[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Double-checking method invocation**\\n\\nI’m looking into using `Method.invoke` with variable arguments, particularly focusing on the last argument as `